Address (High)
0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF  ← Kernel space (inaccessible to user)
──────────────────────────────
     Stack (grows downward)
──────────────────────────────
     Heap (malloc/new)
──────────────────────────────
     Uninitialized data (.bss)
──────────────────────────────
     Initialized data (.data)
──────────────────────────────
     Read-only data (.rodata)
──────────────────────────────
     Code / Text (.text)
──────────────────────────────
0x0000000000000000  ← NULL / invalid memory
Address (Low)



Virtual Address Space (x86-64)
──────────────────────────────────────
0x00007FFFFFFFFFFF  ← user stack top
│
│ Stack
│ Heap
│ Data (.data/.bss/.rodata)
│ Code (.text)
│
0x0000000000400000  ← start of program code
──────────────────────────────────────
0x0000000000000000  ← unmapped
──────────────────────────────────────

Physical Memory (DRAM)
──────────────────────────────────────
[0x0000000000000000] → 4 KB page 0 (used by kernel)
[0x0000000000100000] → page 1 (process A)
[0x0000000000200000] → page 2 (process B)
...
[0x00000003FFFFFFFF] → last usable DRAM page (~16 GB)
──────────────────────────────────────
[Swap Space / Pagefile] → On SSD (if enabled)